activities.message:
Thanks for the recommendation – we're always looking to add more layers of defense.

Here is the ticket filed with Apache: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1803

... and here's a slightly redacted version of the Java code responsible for the vulnerability:

         Url backendURL = ...
         String uri = ctx.getRequest().getRawUri();

         # this line added to patch vuln
         uri = uri.startsWith("/") ? uri : "/" + uri;

         URI proxyUri;
         try {
             proxyUri = new URIBuilder(uri)
                     .setHost(backendURL.getHost())
                     .setPort(backendURL.getPort())
                     .setScheme(backendURL.getScheme())
                     .build();
         } catch (URISyntaxException e) {
             Util.sendError(ctx, 400, INVALID_REQUEST_URL);
             return;
         }

Cheers,
\- Alex
